SIMPLE: seigniory
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seigniory
<hw>Seign"ior*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-ies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>seignorie</ets>, OF.
<ets>seigneurie</ets>, F. <ets>seigneurie</ets>; cf. It.
<ets>signoria</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The power or authority of a
lord; dominion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O'Neal never had any <qex>seigniory</qex> over that country but
what by encroachment he got upon the English.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The territory over which a lord holds jurisdiction;
a manor.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>seigneury</asp>, and
<asp>seignory</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seine</ent>⟦br⟧
